Apollo: the special god of Augustus, made by him to be the protect- ing deity of Rome. According to the Sibyls, Apollo was to reign in the new age: the four preceding saecula having been those of Saturn, Jupiter, Neptune, and Pluto. In this new age was to be a palingenesis, each soul being “after forty times four hundred years ’' reunited with the body which it bad inhabited while on earth (Varro, ap. Augustinum, civ. Dei. xxii. 28). According to other obscure notices, there was to be a series of ten ages, ’ the last of which was that of Apollo, or the Sun.
